      <h3 class="h3">About Street Support Network</h3>
      <p>Street Support Network works online and offline across <a href="https://streetsupport.net/locations/"> 26 locations</a> in the UK, connecting and supporting local people and organisations to tackle homelessness. The network is growing and we anticipate having expanded to 32 locations by early 2022.</p>

      <p>Our website is a central place for people experiencing homelessness to <a href="https://streetsupport.net/find-help/">Find Help</a>, for the general public and business to <a href="https://streetsupport.net/give-help/">Give Help</a> and, via our <a href="http://news.streetsupport.net/">News</a> section, for people to understand more about homelessness, what is being done to address it, and where the challenges and opportunities are.</p>

      <p>We also work offline, connecting people to co-produce better solutions, facilitating conversations and co-ordinating action. Everything we do starts by listening to people with personal insight into homelessness and frontline workers. We use research, co-production, human centered design and creative technology to develop tools and improve systems.</p>

      <h3 class="h3">Purpose of Communications & Engagement Coordinator</h3>

      <p>We’re looking for an experienced Communications & Engagement professional to provide specialist communications for Street Support Network and our partner locations. You will need to communicate more clearly what we do and help the locations spread awareness of their existence and activities and develop their own local brands.</p>

      <p>The successful candidate will provide a professional and high-quality communications service, supporting opportunities to raise our profile, celebrate our achievements and look for new opportunities for growth. This role provides an opportunity to work across many channels, particularly with our expanding digital and social media platforms.</p>

      <p>We envision the successful candidate creating a ‘Best Practice’ bible which includes information, tips, guidance, and other relevant information. This task will involve research, interview and data collection from locations featured in the Network and development and roll out of the bible.</p>

      <p>The Communications & Engagement Coordinator will organise our quarterly UK Network wide events. These events bring together all of our locations to connect, share best practice and challenges and co-create ongoing solutions to tackle homelessness.</p>

      <h3 class="h3">Duties/Responsibilities</h3>

      <ul>
        <li>You must be confident in preparing, planning and project managing the publication of all publicity material to maximise awareness and promote Street Support;</li>
        <li>Having held a similar role, you’ll be experienced in managing social media channels and web content management systems, have excellent English Language skills, and be able to adapt your writing style for different publications, i.e. blogs, newsletters, social media and press releases;</li>
        <li>You must work well within a small team, supporting colleagues in a positive manner that can demonstrate flexibility;</li>
        <li>With your innovative approach, you will create and develop new ways to communicate with stakeholders and update and write engaging web content;</li>
        <li>Further to this you must be confident designing, managing and delivering engaging and successful marketing campaigns, and evaluating their effectiveness;</li>
        <li>You will be responsible for event planning, including understanding the requirements for each event, planning, scheduling speakers, managing all event operations (invitations etc), overseeing event happenings and follow up; and</li>
        <li>Encourage and support effective communications across the network and for individual locations as needed.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="h3">General Duties</h3>

